like in Shock Theater?

460
00:37:21,477 --> 00:37:25,523
Does it matter?
I have some things to say to him.

461
00:37:25,607 --> 00:37:28,151
Maybe you want to come with me?

462
00:37:35,909 --> 00:37:38,328
Christ, Hopley.

463
00:37:38,369 --> 00:37:40,580
- I'm sorry.
- Don't be.

464
00:37:42,081 --> 00:37:44,375
Yours is just a little slower.

465
00:37:44,459 --> 00:37:47,170
You'll get there eventually.

466
00:37:47,253 --> 00:37:49,797
I am not going anywhere.

467
00:37:52,258 --> 00:37:55,678
You find him, Billy.

468
00:37:56,804 --> 00:37:59,015
You find him.

469
00:37:59,098 --> 00:38:00,516
When you do...

470
00:38:04,103 --> 00:38:07,982
I want you to kill that old bastard
and say it's from me.

471
00:38:09,776 --> 00:38:11,110
I can't.

472
00:38:11,194 --> 00:38:13,905
I can't kill him.

473
00:38:13,988 --> 00:38:17,825
I need him to take the curse off.
He's the only one who can, I think.

474
00:38:17,909 --> 00:38:21,871
You think he'll take it off?

475
00:38:21,955 --> 00:38:27,293
Are you gonna snivel up to him
and say, "I'm so sorry"?

476
00:38:27,377 --> 00:38:30,171
Look how sorry I am!

477
00:38:31,089 --> 00:38:32,882
Don't be stupid!

478
00:38:33,925 --> 00:38:38,221
Take the gun! Go on.

479
00:38:39,305 --> 00:38:41,015
Take it.

480
00:38:41,099 --> 00:38:45,228
Take the gun.
Take the gun.

481
00:38:45,311 --> 00:38:47,230
Take the goddamn gun!

482
00:38:48,314 --> 00:38:51,025
Take the gun!
Shoot him!

483
00:38:51,109 --> 00:38:55,905
It's the only satisfaction you'll get,
'cause he'll never take the curse off!

484
00:38:57,615 --> 00:38:59,033
Never!

485
00:39:00,994 --> 00:39:03,663
Never!

486
00:39:04,455 --> 00:39:06,374
[Gunshot]

487
00:39:42,243 --> 00:39:46,748
Mike Houston was here.
Why did you leave the clinic?

488
00:39:47,916 --> 00:39:49,834
Billy?

489
00:39:49,918 --> 00:39:51,836
Are you all right?

490
00:39:54,589 --> 00:39:56,007
Fine.

491
00:39:57,759 --> 00:40:00,470
We care about you, sweetheart.
I care about you.

492
00:40:00,553 --> 00:40:02,013
Linda.

493
00:40:03,765 --> 00:40:06,059
The doctors at the Glassman Clinic
can't help me.

494
00:40:06,142 --> 00:40:09,604
If they can't help you,
who do you think can?

495
00:40:09,687 --> 00:40:12,523
I saw Duncan Hopley
before I came home.

496
00:40:14,943 --> 00:40:17,487
He offered to give me his gun.
I didn't take it.

497
00:40:17,570 --> 00:40:21,157
- Thank God!
- I probably should have, though.

498
00:40:21,241 --> 00:40:23,368
I heard a gunshot after I left.

499
00:40:23,451 --> 00:40:28,039
Maybe Duncan saw a rat and decided
to do a little brain surgery on it...

500
00:40:28,122 --> 00:40:30,041
but I don't think so.

501
00:40:30,124 --> 00:40:33,044
Lempke cursed him too.
His face...

502
00:40:33,127 --> 00:40:37,590
Please. Please! Please don't go
through that curse thing again!

503
00:40:37,674 --> 00:40:39,801
What else can it be?

504
00:40:39,884 --> 00:40:42,262
I'm not on a diet!

505
00:40:42,345 --> 00:40:45,056
It's not anorexia!
I don't have a tapeworm!

506
00:40:45,139 --> 00:40:49,394
I've been eating like mad for six weeks!
12,000 calories a day, at least!

507
00:40:49,477 --> 00:40:51,688
And I'm still losing weight!

508
00:40:52,814 --> 00:40:56,693
I'm being erased.

509
00:41:22,510 --> 00:41:26,014
What about the Glassman?
They keep calling me about you.

510
00:41:26,097 --> 00:41:28,057
Forget the Glassman.

511
00:41:28,099 --> 00:41:32,061
Heidi told me what you said
about this curse thing.

512
00:41:32,103 --> 00:41:35,398
Tells you a lot, doesn't she?
Whispers little secrets in your ear.

513
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:38,067
- What's that supposed to mean?
- Forget it.

514
00:41:38,109 --> 00:41:40,570
All you need to remember
is it's not "a thing."

515
00:41:40,612 --> 00:41:43,573
It's a fact, a curse.

516
00:41:43,615 --> 00:41:46,242
If you don't believe me,
ask Rossington.

517
00:41:46,284 --> 00:41:50,705
Heidi told me what you said about him,
so I called Leda.

518
00:41:50,788 --> 00:41:53,124
He's got skin cancer.
He's being treated.

519
00:41:53,207 --> 00:41:55,668
Skin cancer, my ass.

520
00:41:55,752 --> 00:41:58,213
You are running out of time.

521
00:41:58,296 --> 00:42:01,758
No shit. In two weeks, I won't be able
to go to the bathroom by myself.

522
00:42:01,799 --> 00:42:04,761
- You have to go back to the clinic.
- Wrong.

523
00:42:04,802 --> 00:42:07,430
I have to find those Gypsies.

524
00:42:10,475 --> 00:42:13,895
- Do you see what I'm talking about?
- Yeah, I think he's in trouble.

525
00:42:14,979 --> 00:42:19,275
He's very irrational.
If I were you...

526
00:42:20,818 --> 00:42:22,862
[Engine Starts]

527
00:42:27,533 --> 00:42:29,285
[Heidi] Oh, Mike.

528
00:42:29,369 --> 00:42:30,536
[Tires Squealing]

529
00:42:31,329 --> 00:42:33,248
Tadzu Lempke.

530
00:42:33,331 --> 00:42:37,377
Their king. Also, father of the woman
you struck with your car.

531
00:42:39,671 --> 00:42:41,130
Father?

532
00:42:43,299 --> 00:42:44,884
That's impossible.

533
00:42:44,968 --> 00:42:47,554
That woman was old: 75, 80.

534
00:42:47,637 --> 00:42:50,056
Lempke is 106.

535
00:42:50,139 --> 00:42:54,602
This is his great-granddaughter
and her husband.

536
00:42:54,686 --> 00:42:56,563
106.

537
00:42:56,646 --> 00:43:01,568
He claimed to be 29 when he entered
the country from Europe in 1917.

538
00:43:01,651 --> 00:43:03,903
You figure it out.

539
00:43:03,987 --> 00:43:06,406
You want to talk
about where they're going?

540
00:43:07,699 --> 00:43:09,242
Okay.

541
00:43:09,325 --> 00:43:12,745
I tracked them to Raintree.
Then Milford.

542
00:43:12,829 --> 00:43:14,998
Then Greenough,
which I had never heard of.

543
00:43:15,081 --> 00:43:17,250
Where do you think
they're headed now?

544
00:43:17,333 --> 00:43:19,419
Headed up the Maine coast.

545
00:43:19,502 --> 00:43:23,464
They're always in Bar Harbor at the end
of the season. Pick them up there.

546
00:43:25,341 --> 00:43:27,844
I don't have that much time.

547
00:43:47,780 --> 00:43:50,700
[Mike] I have the order.
All you have to do is sign it.

548
00:43:50,783 --> 00:43:54,537
[Heidi] To sign it?
I don't know.

549
00:43:54,621 --> 00:43:57,373
Maybe you're right.

550
00:43:57,457 --> 00:44:01,377
[Mike] I know you don't want to,
but it's best for both of us.

551
00:44:01,461 --> 00:44:04,756
[Heidi] If we take legal action,
what will he do when he finds out?

552
00:44:04,839 --> 00:44:06,382
What kind of legal action?

553
00:44:14,140 --> 00:44:18,061
The kind that forces you back to the
Glassman Clinic before it's too late.

554
00:44:27,445 --> 00:44:28,821
Okay.

555
00:44:28,905 --> 00:44:30,698
I'll go back.

556
00:44:30,782 --> 00:44:33,201
Oh, Billy!

557
00:44:33,284 --> 00:44:36,204
I am so happy.

558
00:44:46,130 --> 00:44:49,342
Dear Heidi,
I'm going after Lempke.

559
00:44:49,425 --> 00:44:52,053
The old guy knows what I did,
but not what you did.

560
00:44:52,136 --> 00:44:55,390
That frees you up to believe
the curse is in my head.

561
00:44:55,473 --> 00:45:00,186
Unfortunately, that's a luxury
I no longer have. I'll work it out.

562
00:45:00,270 --> 00:45:04,065
In the meantime, if there's anything
going on between you and Dr. Mikey...

563
00:45:04,148 --> 00:45:06,109
end it, immediately.

564
00:45:06,150 --> 00:45:07,610
Billy.

565
00:45:56,618 --> 00:45:58,119
[Man]
Biff Quigley.

566
00:45:58,202 --> 00:46:02,624
Call me Biff. Mind telling me
why you want to know where they went?

567
00:46:03,958 --> 00:46:06,836
- Yes, Biff, I mind.
- Fine.

568
00:46:07,712 --> 00:46:09,047
Bill?

569
00:46:09,130 --> 00:46:11,216
A man's reasons ought to be his own.

570
00:46:11,299 --> 00:46:15,386
Good. Now, since we agree
on all that...

571
00:46:15,470 --> 00:46:19,015
But it's still going to cost you $800.

572
00:46:20,016 --> 00:46:23,519
- What?
- The info is a freebie.

573
00:46:24,479 --> 00:46:27,023
The $800 is for the info...

574
00:46:27,106 --> 00:46:31,152
I don't give your wife and doctor.

575
00:46:39,786 --> 00:46:41,704
Do you take travelers' checks?

576
00:47:24,956 --> 00:47:26,416
Gotcha.

577
00:47:32,422 --> 00:47:38,177
[Woman] Come let the Gypsy king
guess your weight and tell your fate.

578
00:47:39,762 --> 00:47:41,222
Don't be shy.

579
00:47:41,306 --> 00:47:44,350
The old man, he knows everything.

580
00:47:46,227 --> 00:47:48,062
He can see everything.

581
00:47:48,146 --> 00:47:51,357
Don't bother
to step on the scale.

582
00:47:51,441 --> 00:47:54,152
I can tell your weight
from right here.

583
00:47:54,235 --> 00:47:58,031
159, right?

584
00:47:58,114 --> 00:47:59,782
And next week...

585
00:47:59,866 --> 00:48:02,702
gonna be 143.

586
00:48:02,785 --> 00:48:05,371
And the week after that...
Ooh!

587
00:48:05,455 --> 00:48:08,625
We don't like to think
about that, do we, mister?

588
00:48:08,708 --> 00:48:11,753
[Laughing, Wheezing]

589
00:48:14,172 --> 00:48:17,217
Sorry, mister, but you lose.

590
00:48:19,636 --> 00:48:21,054
But let's see.

591
00:48:26,351 --> 00:48:28,269
No.

592
00:48:33,358 --> 00:48:36,527
Ah, yes.

593
00:48:41,741 --> 00:48:44,577
You can have a prize anyway.

594
00:48:47,664 --> 00:48:49,582
Haaah!

595
00:48:50,375 --> 00:48:52,126
Haaah!

596
00:48:54,295 --> 00:48:56,214
[Laughing]

597
00:49:01,928 --> 00:49:03,596
[Screaming]

598
00:49:05,598 --> 00:49:07,600
[Tires Screeching]

599
00:49:08,518 --> 00:49:11,020
Billy, get in, you idiot!

600
00:49:11,104 --> 00:49:12,814
Cary?

601
00:49:12,897 --> 00:49:14,607
Hey-ah!

602
00:49:18,319 --> 00:49:20,405
[Screaming]

603
00:49:23,074 --> 00:49:27,704
You ready, Billy? You and I
are gonna get that Gypsy bastard!

604
00:49:28,913 --> 00:49:30,331
[Billy]
What are you doing?

605
00:49:30,415 --> 00:49:34,335
I'm saving you, Billy.
Isn't that what you want?

606
00:49:34,419 --> 00:49:35,962
[Cary Laughs]

607
00:49:36,045 --> 00:49:37,255
[Laughing]

608
00:49:44,762 --> 00:49:46,848
[Cary Laughing]

609
00:49:48,349 --> 00:49:50,226
[Cary]
Hold on, partner!

610
00:50:03,615 --> 00:50:05,533
[Screaming]

611
00:50:07,118 --> 00:50:12,040
[Gasping]

612
00:50:23,134 --> 00:50:27,889
Leda, this is Billy Halleck.
Can I speak with Cary, please?

613
00:50:27,972 --> 00:50:32,393
Sorry, Billy. Cary can't come
to the phone right now.

614
00:50:32,477 --> 00:50:36,064
Yesterday he drove his Lincoln
into a gas truck.

615
00:50:36,147 --> 00:50:38,733
A happy ending of sorts.

616
00:50:38,816 --> 00:50:41,736
He always did want to be cremated.

617
00:50:41,819 --> 00:50:44,906
[Phone Clicking,
Dial Tone Humming]

618
00:50:44,989 --> 00:50:47,575
I'm sorry, Leda.

619
00:51:35,290 --> 00:51:37,750
Excuse me.
You seen this man?

620
00:51:38,835 --> 00:51:40,420
His name's Tadzu Lempke.

621
00:51:43,131 --> 00:51:44,549
Taddy Lempke?

622
00:51:51,472 --> 00:51:53,391
I knew he was around.

623
00:51:53,474 --> 00:51:56,227
- You know Lempke?
- How could you forget him?

624
00:51:56,311 --> 00:51:59,731
Big, black cancer
in the middle of his face.

625
00:51:59,814 --> 00:52:03,401
I hadn't seen him
since I worked the Ferris wheel...

626
00:52:03,484 --> 00:52:07,071
ten, maybe twenty years ago.

627
00:52:07,155 --> 00:52:10,575
But it was him last night.
You know what he said to me?

628
00:52:11,951 --> 00:52:14,495
"Hey, Flash.

629
00:52:14,579 --> 00:52:18,666
Where that pretty
little wife of yours?

630
00:52:20,001 --> 00:52:23,087
Well, don't matter.

631
00:52:23,171 --> 00:52:26,257
You'll see her soon."

632
00:52:28,760 --> 00:52:31,888
Mister, my wife has been dead
for five years...

633
00:52:31,971 --> 00:52:34,015
and he knew it.

634
00:52:40,772 --> 00:52:44,359
Did you see which way the Gypsies went
when they left here?

635
00:52:44,442 --> 00:52:46,611
No, but I heard them.

636
00:52:46,694 --> 00:52:49,739
You can't miss the sound
of those old beaters they drive.

637
00:52:49,822 --> 00:52:53,243
Out 27, then north on 1.

638
00:52:57,121 --> 00:53:00,416
Listen. Thank you.

639
00:53:01,626 --> 00:53:03,586
Thank you very much.

640
00:53:06,297 --> 00:53:09,259
Mister, be careful.

641
00:53:09,342 --> 00:53:12,011
That Taddy will chew you up
and swallow you down.

642
00:53:17,141 --> 00:53:18,434
[Linda] Yes?

643
00:53:20,478 --> 00:53:21,604
Linda.

644
00:53:21,688 --> 00:53:24,941
Daddy, where are you?
I've been so worried.

645
00:53:24,983 --> 00:53:27,860
It's good to hear your voice.
When did you get home?

646
00:53:27,944 --> 00:53:30,405
Yesterday.
Mom's really upset.

647
00:53:30,488 --> 00:53:32,865
Where is she now?

648
00:53:32,949 --> 00:53:35,285
She's in the kitchen
with Dr. Houston.

649
00:53:35,326 --> 00:53:37,537
[Billy]
What's Dr. Mikey doing there?

650
00:53:37,620 --> 00:53:41,416
- He's been here a lot. Why?
- Billy, is that you?

651
00:53:43,126 --> 00:53:46,379
Sweetheart, I've been talking to Mike,
and he's been saying that...

652
00:53:46,462 --> 00:53:48,548
Bitch! Bitch!

653
00:53:48,631 --> 00:53:51,384
This is all your fault, you bitch!

654
00:54:57,116 --> 00:54:59,327
For shame! My mama!

655
00:54:59,410 --> 00:55:02,247
I say you killed my own mama!

656
00:55:02,330 --> 00:55:06,042
I say you are a demon,
and we should kill you!

657
00:55:06,084 --> 00:55:11,214
Is that what I am to you?
A demon?

658
00:55:12,966 --> 00:55:14,551
Look at me.

659
00:55:17,011 --> 00:55:19,013
[Speaking Foreign Language]

660
00:55:27,480 --> 00:55:32,819
She call you
the white man from town.

661
00:55:33,945 --> 00:55:36,781
You got no business with us...

662
00:55:36,864 --> 00:55:39,534
and we got no business with you.

663
00:55:39,576 --> 00:55:42,328
- Go away.
- [Speaking Foreign Language]

664
00:55:42,412 --> 00:55:44,330
I'm not through with you.

665
00:55:45,540 --> 00:55:50,211
Your daughter ran out
between two parked cars.

666
00:55:50,295 --> 00:55:51,880
I couldn't see her.

667
00:55:51,963 --> 00:55:54,841
Why wasn't you watching,
white man from town?

668
00:55:54,924 --> 00:55:57,385
Why wasn't you watching?

669
00:55:57,468 --> 00:55:59,596
You never see us!

670
00:56:01,723 --> 00:56:04,058
- Cha!
- Fa!

671
00:56:05,143 --> 00:56:09,772
Doing this to me
won't bring your daughter back.

672
00:56:09,814 --> 00:56:12,734
Duncan Hopley is dead.

673
00:56:12,775 --> 00:56:14,903
So is Cary Rossington.

674
00:56:14,944 --> 00:56:17,071
Neither of them
brought your daughter back.

675
00:56:17,155 --> 00:56:22,076
Justice ain't about bringing
back the dead, white man.

676
00:56:22,160 --> 00:56:24,662
Justice is about justice!

677
00:56:24,746 --> 00:56:27,665
Your friends,
the policeman and the judge...

678
00:56:27,749 --> 00:56:31,127
make sure nothing happen to you,
they keep you safe.

679
00:56:31,169 --> 00:56:34,339
But I make sure
something happen to them.

680
00:56:34,422 --> 00:56:38,134
That justice, white man.
Gypsy justice.

681
00:56:38,218 --> 00:56:43,014
You know as much about justice
as I know about turbine engines.

682
00:56:43,097 --> 00:56:45,183
Now take your fucking curse
off of me!

683
00:56:50,772 --> 00:56:53,524
I never take it off.

684
00:56:53,608 --> 00:56:56,527
I die with it in me mouth.

685
00:57:08,998 --> 00:57:11,501
I'm sorry.
It was my fault.

686
00:57:11,584 --> 00:57:14,796
Please.
I'm asking you nicely.

687
00:57:14,837 --> 00:57:18,466
Take it off
before this goes any further.

688
00:57:18,550 --> 00:57:21,469
Get out or I make it worse.

689
00:57:21,553 --> 00:57:26,558
I make it so much worse,
you think I bless you the first time.

690
00:57:26,641 --> 00:57:28,142
Like this.

691
00:57:58,923 --> 00:58:01,009
Okay, I'll go...

692
00:58:01,092 --> 00:58:03,428
but not before I curse you...

693
00:58:05,096 --> 00:58:08,433
and everybody I see
by the light of this fire!

694
00:58:08,516 --> 00:58:11,060
The curse
of the white man from town!

695
00:58:11,853 --> 00:58:15,023
[Laughing, Wheezing]

696
00:58:30,204 --> 00:58:33,333
That's right, laugh.

697
00:58:33,416 --> 00:58:36,753
Laugh now, cry later...

698
00:58:36,794 --> 00:58:39,923
when this all is at your feet!

699
00:58:40,006 --> 00:58:42,926
You want to see what
the white man from town can do...

700
00:58:42,967 --> 00:58:45,803
when he puts his mind to it?

701
00:58:47,096 --> 00:58:48,932
Don't make me start, old man!

702
00:58:49,015 --> 00:58:51,267
Don't make me start!

703
00:58:51,309 --> 00:58:53,478
Take it off while you still can!

704
00:58:57,941 --> 00:59:00,276
[Speaking Foreign Language]

705
00:59:00,318 --> 00:59:03,947
Get out of here!
Leave this camp, murdering bastard!

706
00:59:21,673 --> 00:59:23,633
Look at this!

707
00:59:28,263 --> 00:59:31,307
The curse
of the white man from town...

708
00:59:33,560 --> 00:59:35,228
is on you, pal.

709
00:59:36,563 --> 00:59:40,316
They don't write about it in books,
but it is on you.

710
00:59:49,325 --> 00:59:51,160
This is Billy Halleck.

711
00:59:51,244 --> 00:59:53,955
- Can I speak to Richie Ginelli?
- Hold on.

712
00:59:56,749 --> 00:59:59,043
William.
How you doing, Counselor?

713
00:59:59,127 --> 01:00:03,047
Not so good, Richie.
I need a doctor.

714
01:00:03,131 --> 01:00:07,260
I'll have someone to you by morning.
Not a doctor, but he's pretty close.

715
01:00:16,311 --> 01:00:18,229
Ball bearing, huh?

716
01:00:21,816 --> 01:00:23,234
First for me.

717
01:00:26,529 --> 01:00:29,532
This kind of pain
is a first for me.

718
01:00:30,950 --> 01:00:33,536
There's a reason for that.

719
01:00:35,788 --> 01:00:38,875
I've worked with cadavers
that looked better than you do.

720
01:00:46,424 --> 01:00:50,386
These are mine,
but you need them more than I do.

721
01:00:50,470 --> 01:00:51,888
Potassium tablets.

722
01:00:55,058 --> 01:00:57,936
Will they do anything
for the pain?

723
01:00:58,019 --> 01:00:59,062
No.

724
01:01:00,188 --> 01:01:02,690
They'll prevent you
from going into cardiac arrest.

725
01:01:06,486 --> 01:01:11,199
Look, if it's a diet,
you can come off it now.

726
01:01:11,241 --> 01:01:13,201
You have my permission.

727
01:01:20,500 --> 01:01:23,294
Expect a visitor tomorrow.

728
01:01:26,381 --> 01:01:28,466
Who?

729
01:01:28,550 --> 01:01:31,386
Take the Bufferin
and get some rest.

730
01:02:05,587 --> 01:02:07,589
[Knock At Door]

731
01:02:17,140 --> 01:02:21,769
You should have called me earlier,
Billy. A lot earlier.

732
01:02:21,853 --> 01:02:24,606
I didn't expect you
to come yourself.

733
01:02:24,647 --> 01:02:27,859
Hey, I wouldn't have missed it
for the world.

734
01:02:35,199 --> 01:02:37,160
Okay, I got it.

735
01:02:38,828 --> 01:02:40,246
Fuck.

736
01:02:41,331 --> 01:02:42,582
Fuck!

737
01:03:04,270 --> 01:03:05,688
Who was I kidding?

738
01:03:12,654 --> 01:03:17,200
You ever hear of something
called "committal in absentia"?

739
01:03:20,703 --> 01:03:22,372
Sure.

740
01:03:22,413 --> 01:03:27,210
It means somebody's committed to a
mental hospital without being examined.

741
01:03:27,252 --> 01:03:30,338
It's usually invoked when some guy
goes loony and runs off.

742
01:03:33,591 --> 01:03:35,051
Christ.

743
01:03:39,347 --> 01:03:42,225
Houston couldn't have done it
without Heidi.

744
01:03:44,394 --> 01:03:45,812
Damn them.

745
01:03:47,522 --> 01:03:49,524
Damn them both.

746
01:03:55,238 --> 01:03:57,740
Her and this doctor,
you don't think...

747
01:03:59,284 --> 01:04:01,286
Yeah. Sure.

748
01:04:02,620 --> 01:04:05,456
I didn't want to believe it...

749
01:04:05,540 --> 01:04:09,043
until one night I saw his car
pulling out of the driveway.

750
01:04:10,587 --> 01:04:13,089
She said he just dropped by.

751
01:04:16,551 --> 01:04:20,930
Hey, relax.
You got nothing to worry about.

752
01:04:21,014 --> 01:04:24,642
By the time the order goes through,
this will either be over...

753
01:04:24,726 --> 01:04:27,020
or you'll be dead.

754
01:04:27,103 --> 01:04:32,358
If you make it, you can
deal with them at your leisure.

755
01:04:44,621 --> 01:04:48,708
I'm gonna get you for this, Heidi.

756
01:04:48,791 --> 01:04:51,377
I swear I am.

757
01:05:08,686 --> 01:05:10,897
Richie.

758
01:05:10,980 --> 01:05:14,609
You're not actually
gonna hurt anybody, are you?

759
01:05:14,651 --> 01:05:16,069
No.

760
01:05:16,152 --> 01:05:18,988
But, Billy, if I'm gonna help you...

761
01:05:19,072 --> 01:05:21,908
you can't ask that question again.

762
01:05:30,333 --> 01:05:34,921
[Dogs Barking]

763
01:05:38,216 --> 01:05:39,509
[Barking]

764
01:05:39,592 --> 01:05:44,681
Hey, hey, hey.
What do you say, fellas?

765
01:05:44,764 --> 01:05:47,016
Do I smell like a gyp?

766
01:05:50,270 --> 01:05:53,356
Who wants a little strychnine?

767
01:05:53,439 --> 01:05:55,608
Here you go.
Here you go.

768
01:06:42,405 --> 01:06:45,950
Hey, kid, wake up.
It's a visit from the money fairy.

769
01:06:50,580 --> 01:06:52,040
What's your name?

770
01:06:52,081 --> 01:06:54,834
Spurton. Frank Spurton.

771
01:06:56,502 --> 01:06:59,839
Okay, Frank Spurton.
Check it out.

772
01:07:15,271 --> 01:07:18,733
I don't do nothing
that goes on video.

773
01:07:18,816 --> 01:07:21,402
That's a good plan, Stan.

774
01:07:21,444 --> 01:07:26,074
Listen. There's some Gypsies
camped out up the road.

775
01:07:26,115 --> 01:07:28,993
They light, you call me.

776
01:07:33,748 --> 01:07:36,751
Who do I ask for
in case someone else answers?

777
01:07:36,834 --> 01:07:40,380
Don't worry.
I'll answer.

778
01:08:03,778 --> 01:08:08,449
- You like this, don't you?
- Like it? Are you kidding?

779
01:08:08,491 --> 01:08:10,785
I fuckin' love it!

780
01:08:13,538 --> 01:08:15,331
[Telephone Ringing]

781
01:08:16,958 --> 01:08:20,962
- Yeah.
- They're at a small farm off Route 92.

782
01:08:21,045 --> 01:08:22,964
I think they made me.

783
01:08:23,006 --> 01:08:26,718
If I were you, friend,
I'd get out of there as soon as I could.

784
01:08:26,801 --> 01:08:28,469
And lose my number.

785
01:08:55,872 --> 01:08:57,290
Thanks.

786
01:09:02,921 --> 01:09:04,505
Well, well, well.

787
01:09:18,645 --> 01:09:20,063
Hey, Billy.

788
01:09:47,632 --> 01:09:51,010
I think it's time
for us to move on.

789
01:09:57,600 --> 01:10:02,021
- This is getting out of hand.
- Wrong.

790
01:10:02,105 --> 01:10:04,190
This has been out of hand...

791
01:10:04,274 --> 01:10:06,442
ever since that old gyp
touched you.

792
01:10:06,526 --> 01:10:10,655
I'm just the guy
to put it back "in hand."

793
01:10:10,738 --> 01:10:13,658
I gotta show them
they can't get away with that stuff...

794
01:10:13,741 --> 01:10:16,202
they pulled on that kid.

795
01:10:16,286 --> 01:10:20,206
He was a mook,
but he was my mook.

796
01:10:20,290 --> 01:10:22,208
Richie the Hammer.

797
01:10:23,543 --> 01:10:25,128
Please don't.

798
01:10:31,801 --> 01:10:34,429
## [Violin Playing]

799
01:11:12,467 --> 01:11:13,468
[Screaming]

800
01:11:37,408 --> 01:11:40,036
[Grunting]

801
01:11:43,414 --> 01:11:45,041
There! Over there!

802
01:11:57,887 --> 01:11:59,389
No!

803
01:12:02,684 --> 01:12:04,602
Nooo!

804
01:12:07,939 --> 01:12:09,357
No!

805
01:12:10,567 --> 01:12:12,110
Gabe!

806
01:12:13,236 --> 01:12:16,698
No, Gabe!

807
01:12:17,615 --> 01:12:19,909
No! [Crying]

808
01:12:41,764 --> 01:12:44,893
- Yes?
- F.B.I.

809
01:12:44,934 --> 01:12:49,898
Special Agent Stoner.
I have a few questions, Mrs. Grimani.

810
01:12:49,981 --> 01:12:52,317
Can you identify...

811
01:12:53,776 --> 01:12:57,196
That pig killed my old mama!

812
01:12:57,947 --> 01:13:01,075
- He killed my husband.
- Mr. William Halleck?

813
01:13:01,117 --> 01:13:03,661
Was it him
at this camp last night?

814
01:13:03,745 --> 01:13:08,583
No, but we believe he hired someone
to make the attack.

815
01:13:08,625 --> 01:13:10,585
We have him in custody.

816
01:13:10,627 --> 01:13:14,923
Would you mind accompanying me
to identify him personally?

817
01:13:21,971 --> 01:13:24,349
[Car Doors Slamming]

818
01:13:29,270 --> 01:13:31,189
My God.

819
01:13:32,106 --> 01:13:33,524
Not again.

820
01:13:37,195 --> 01:13:39,155
He's waiting in the car.

821
01:13:45,995 --> 01:13:47,956
There is no car here.

822
01:13:47,997 --> 01:13:51,542
I almost forgot.

823
01:13:51,626 --> 01:13:55,547
I have a photo of the man we suspect
attacked your camp.

824
01:13:55,630 --> 01:13:56,673
It was you!

825
01:14:04,138 --> 01:14:05,640
Acid, bitch.

826
01:14:05,682 --> 01:14:07,809
[Screaming]

827
01:14:14,607 --> 01:14:17,026
You scream again,
and I'll kill you.

828
01:14:20,238 --> 01:14:22,574
You just got a face full
of soda pop and baking soda.

829
01:14:22,657 --> 01:14:23,992
[Screaming]

830
01:14:31,374 --> 01:14:32,875
Billy, get out!

831
01:14:37,630 --> 01:14:40,049
- [Gun Cocking]
- Richie, no!

832
01:14:42,594 --> 01:14:45,638
This time you live
because my friend asks.

833
01:14:45,722 --> 01:14:49,017
Next time,
you're one dead little whore.

834
01:14:50,560 --> 01:14:52,520
Fuck you.
And fuck him!

835
01:14:53,688 --> 01:14:54,772
[Spitting]

836
01:14:56,858 --> 01:14:58,234
Now...

837
01:14:59,152 --> 01:15:04,073
here's the real deal.

838
01:15:08,745 --> 01:15:11,039
[Gasping]

839
01:15:11,080 --> 01:15:14,417
Now here's what I want you to do.

840
01:15:16,753 --> 01:15:20,715
Unless you want
to wear a Gypsy scarf...

841
01:15:20,798 --> 01:15:23,968
over your face
for the rest of your life...

842
01:15:25,553 --> 01:15:31,226
hold very still!

843
01:15:35,605 --> 01:15:38,650
Tell the old gyp to meet me
at the lighthouse in two hours.

844
01:16:11,849 --> 01:16:15,937
Your friend is a pig!
He will die thin!

845
01:16:16,020 --> 01:16:19,941
But you will die first,
you bastard!

846
01:16:34,455 --> 01:16:38,626
He'll meet you there in about an hour,
over by that bench.

847
01:16:40,587 --> 01:16:41,921
Thanks, Richie.

848
01:16:45,508 --> 01:16:49,846
You want to thank me?
Get that old bastard.

849
01:17:02,775 --> 01:17:05,320
[Car Engine Starts]

850
01:17:28,676 --> 01:17:30,094
Wake up.

851
01:17:31,554 --> 01:17:32,847
Wake up.

852
01:17:35,099 --> 01:17:37,602
[Sniffing]

853
01:17:38,770 --> 01:17:43,441
Your dreams smell bad to me.
They stink.

854
01:17:43,524 --> 01:17:46,986
Maybe you think
you're still dreaming, huh?

855
01:17:53,409 --> 01:17:58,706
Does this look like dream to you,
white man from town?

856
01:17:58,748 --> 01:18:02,669
You kill my daughter,
and you get off.

857
01:18:02,752 --> 01:18:06,381
For that you deserve to die,
so I curse you!

858
01:18:06,422 --> 01:18:11,219
But now, I got to do this
so your crazy friend...

859
01:18:11,261 --> 01:18:14,097
don't hurt my Galina.

860
01:18:14,138 --> 01:18:18,893
Already he kill her husband.
You want your little girl hurt?

861
01:18:19,936 --> 01:18:23,273
I didn't want any of this.

862
01:18:23,356 --> 01:18:25,692
You want to get rid of the curse?

863
01:18:25,775 --> 01:18:28,820
First, you've got to give it...

864
01:18:28,903 --> 01:18:31,114
to this pie.

865
01:18:37,495 --> 01:18:42,000
Then you give this pie...

866
01:18:43,459 --> 01:18:45,753
[Gasping]

867
01:18:45,795 --> 01:18:49,841
With the curse inside,
to somebody else.

868
01:18:52,802 --> 01:18:56,431
[Lempke Chanting]

869
01:19:01,185 --> 01:19:04,772
[Chanting]

870
01:19:05,523 --> 01:19:06,649
Okay.

871
01:19:09,235 --> 01:19:12,697
You gain weight quick now.

872
01:19:12,780 --> 01:19:17,118
So quick, you don't know
what's going on.

873
01:19:17,160 --> 01:19:20,330
But somebody...

874
01:19:20,413 --> 01:19:23,875
got to eat this pie soon.

875
01:19:23,958 --> 01:19:28,213
Everyone who eat pie
die quick and bad.

876
01:19:28,880 --> 01:19:31,716
You got somebody?

877
01:19:31,799 --> 01:19:33,760
Yes.

878
01:19:33,843 --> 01:19:37,722
Yeah, you got somebody.

879
01:19:52,570 --> 01:19:57,367
But why you don't do right?
Eat your own pie.

880
01:19:57,408 --> 01:20:00,536
You die thin,
but you die clean.

881
01:20:02,413 --> 01:20:04,582
Get away from me.

882
01:20:04,666 --> 01:20:07,126
Our business is done.

883
01:20:17,220 --> 01:20:21,432
Die clean, white man from town.

884
01:20:21,516 --> 01:20:23,518
Die clean.

885
01:20:35,405 --> 01:20:40,285
- Daddy, are you okay?
- I'm still thin, but I'll be fine.

886
01:20:40,368 --> 01:20:43,580
Listen.
Daddy's coming home tonight...

887
01:20:43,663 --> 01:20:45,582
but I want it to be a surprise, okay?

888
01:20:45,623 --> 01:20:47,417
Yeah. Sure.

889
01:20:47,500 --> 01:20:50,628
- I want you to stay at Georgia's.
- Daddy, no!

890
01:20:50,712 --> 01:20:53,006
Yes.

891
01:20:53,089 --> 01:20:54,549
There are some things...

892
01:20:54,632 --> 01:20:58,094
I need to talk
to your mother about.

893
01:20:58,136 --> 01:20:59,762
Promise you'll stay at Georgia's.

894
01:20:59,846 --> 01:21:01,890
- All right.
- Thanks, honey.

895
01:21:01,931 --> 01:21:03,808
Let me talk with your mother.

896
01:21:05,852 --> 01:21:07,729
Billy, is that you?

897
01:21:09,522 --> 01:21:12,567
There are some things I have to do
before I come home.

898
01:21:12,650 --> 01:21:14,652
I'll see you
in a couple of days.

899
01:22:03,534 --> 01:22:05,495
Wake up...

900
01:22:05,578 --> 01:22:09,958
white woman from town.

901
01:22:09,999 --> 01:22:12,210
[Gasps]
Oh, Billy.

902
01:22:12,293 --> 01:22:13,628
Oh, Billy! Oh!

903
01:22:13,670 --> 01:22:16,965
Whoa. At least wait
until I get up to 140.

904
01:22:17,006 --> 01:22:19,551
I didn't expect you home
until the end of the week.

905
01:22:19,634 --> 01:22:22,720
I couldn't wait to see you.
I even brought you a present.

906
01:22:23,846 --> 01:22:25,848
It's on the kitchen counter.

907
01:22:25,890 --> 01:22:30,353
I know why you came home early.
I know what you've been thinking.

908
01:22:30,436 --> 01:22:35,149
I swear there's never been anything
between Mike Houston and me.

909
01:22:35,191 --> 01:22:38,778
We can talk about it
in the morning.

910
01:22:38,861 --> 01:22:42,782
I'm gonna go upstairs.
I'm exhausted.

911
01:22:43,950 --> 01:22:45,785
All right.

912
01:22:47,870 --> 01:22:50,665
- I'm going with you.
- No, no.

913
01:22:50,707 --> 01:22:52,750
It's early.

914
01:22:52,834 --> 01:22:56,296
Why don't you check out
what I brought you?

915
01:22:56,379 --> 01:22:59,048
You're gonna like it.

916
01:22:59,132 --> 01:23:01,843
You sound like
your old silly self.

917
01:23:01,885 --> 01:23:04,387
I'm starting to feel
like my old silly self again.

918
01:23:04,470 --> 01:23:06,389
- Take a look.
- It's in there?

919
01:23:06,472 --> 01:23:07,891
Go. Go.

920
01:23:17,233 --> 01:23:19,152
Is it strawberry?

921
01:23:19,235 --> 01:23:20,695
Uh-huh.

922
01:23:20,737 --> 01:23:23,698
Oh, Billy,
that's my favorite.

923
01:23:24,908 --> 01:23:26,367
I know.

924
01:23:31,414 --> 01:23:36,878
Getting even is also
what it's all about, you bitch.

925
01:23:55,146 --> 01:23:56,439
Heidi?

926
01:23:59,234 --> 01:24:01,236
[In Singsong Voice]
Heidi.

927
01:24:02,445 --> 01:24:03,863
You awake?

928
01:24:10,787 --> 01:24:12,705
Did you try it?

929
01:24:19,295 --> 01:24:22,048
Yep. You tried it.

930
01:24:43,570 --> 01:24:45,822
Strawberry pie.

931
01:24:45,905 --> 01:24:47,949
Mmm.

932
01:24:53,580 --> 01:24:57,959
I wouldn't want to eat too much
of it myself, though.

933
01:24:58,001 --> 01:25:00,044
It's diet food.

934
01:25:13,892 --> 01:25:15,476
Look at you.

935
01:25:16,811 --> 01:25:20,565
Size six again.
Maybe even a size four.

936
01:26:05,944 --> 01:26:07,612
Daddy!

937
01:26:09,280 --> 01:26:13,576
You look so thin,
but I'm glad to see you anyway.

938
01:26:16,037 --> 01:26:17,956
I'm sorry I didn't stay
at Georgia's...

939
01:26:18,039 --> 01:26:21,417
but I needed to talk to Mom
before I saw you.

940
01:26:21,501 --> 01:26:23,503
Things haven't been great
between us...

941
01:26:23,586 --> 01:26:25,547
because of what
you've been going through.

942
01:26:25,630 --> 01:26:27,549
So I came back
after you went to sleep.

943
01:26:27,590 --> 01:26:29,717
We worked things out.

944
01:26:29,801 --> 01:26:32,887
And I just had a piece of your pie
for breakfast.

945
01:26:32,971 --> 01:26:35,557
- You had...
- Yes, Dad. It was delicious.

946
01:26:35,640 --> 01:26:39,102
And things are cool
between Mom and I.

947
01:26:39,185 --> 01:26:42,397
I have to play soccer with Lisa,
but I'll catch you later.

948
01:26:47,193 --> 01:26:48,611
Bye. Love you.

949
01:26:52,323 --> 01:26:54,701
My God, what have I done?

950
01:27:15,054 --> 01:27:17,307
[Doorbell Ringing]

951
01:27:24,647 --> 01:27:27,817
Billy, you're home.

952
01:27:27,901 --> 01:27:29,861
Dr. Mikey.

953
01:27:29,944 --> 01:27:32,655
Early for a house call, isn't it?

954
01:27:35,158 --> 01:27:37,118
It's not what you think.

955
01:27:38,786 --> 01:27:41,664
Heidi was upset.

956
01:27:41,748 --> 01:27:44,167
I just stopped by
to see how she was doing.

957
01:27:44,208 --> 01:27:48,796
Don't sweat it. I might have done
the same thing in your shoes.

958
01:27:48,838 --> 01:27:51,883
After all,
I was acting like a jerk.

959
01:27:51,966 --> 01:27:56,679
But I'm fine now.
Even put a little weight back on.

960
01:27:56,763 --> 01:27:59,891
I was just digging into a slice
of this breakfast pie.

961
01:27:59,974 --> 01:28:03,186
- Care to join me?
- I really shouldn't.

962
01:28:03,228 --> 01:28:07,690
Come on, Mike.
I've settled everything with Heidi.

963
01:28:07,774 --> 01:28:11,569
Now it's your turn.
The pie's delicious.

964
01:28:11,653 --> 01:28:13,571
You sure I'm not intruding?

965
01:28:13,655 --> 01:28:15,198
Positive...

966
01:28:20,328 --> 01:28:22,705
white doctor from town.

